item.description: This parameter is 1 or 0. 1 = normal status 0 = may have reached max_connections

item.name: Net - connections in the que
item.description: An obscure named statistic counting the number of times memcached has hit its connection limit. When memcached hits the max connections setting, it disables its listener and new connections will wait in a queue. When someone disconnects, memcached wakes up the listener and starts accepting again.

item.name: Net - yield connection
item.description: Number of times any connection yielded to another due to hitting the -R limit.

item.name: Objects - evicted unused items before expiring
item.description: Items pulled from LRU that were never touched by get/incr/append/etc before expiring.
